feat: Add a new feature.
fix: Fix errors or bugs.
refactor: Restructure code without changing behavior.
docs: Change or add documentation.
style: Change code formatting (e.g., indentation, whitespace) without affecting the code's meaning.
test: Add or modify test cases.
chore: Changes not directly related to users or source code (e.g., update build tasks).
perf: Improve performance.
build: Changes that affect the build system.
ci: Changes related to continuous integration or continuous delivery (CI/CD).
